    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5914/30½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State ad interim</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">16 June, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have read these papers
                    through with close attention, and thank you for handing them to me.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d322fn1">Papers concerning negotiations with Denmark, 1899–1902; for
                        correspondence previously printed on these earlier negotiation, see <ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_457">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign relation</hi>, 1917, pp. 457</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_544">544</ref>; for correspondence previously
                        printed concerning negotiations with Denmark in 1915, 1916, and 1917, see
                            <ref target="frus1917#pg_588">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pp. 588</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_706">706</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>As I said to you yesterday, I am, and have long been, deeply interested in the
                    purchase of the Danish West Indies. I hope that you will take the matter up very
                    seriously and that it may be possible to have a concrete proposal, if possible
                    in the form of a treaty, to lay before the Senate at its next session.</p>
                <p>Cordially and Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
